    • Constructor Detail

      • GeomagneticField

        public GeomagneticField​(float latitude,
                        float longitude,
                        float hae,
                        long millis)
        Estimate the magnetic field at a given point and time.
        Parameters:
        latitude - Latitude in WGS84 geodetic coordinates -- positive is east.
        longitude - Longitude in WGS84 geodetic coordinates -- positive is north.
        hae - Altitude in WGS84 geodetic coordinates, in meters (HAE).
        millis - Time at which to evaluate the declination, in milliseconds since January 1, 1970. (approximate is fine -- the declination changes very slowly).

        public static double getDeclination​(double latitude,
                                    double longitude,
                                    double hae)
        Returns:
        The declination of the horizontal component of the magnetic field from true north, in degrees (i.e. positive means the magnetic field is rotated east that much from true north).
